‐Don't call us stupid!

306
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,654
Just shut up and follow me.

307
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:38,156
Okay.

308
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:41,784
Tom‐Tom seems kind of different
tonight, wouldn't you agree?

309
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:42,827
Yeah.

310
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:48,166
♪

311
00:11:52,295 --> 00:11:57,967
♪

312
00:11:59,886 --> 00:12:01,554
You guys know about that clock?

313
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:03,681
Yeah, the frozen clock, right?

314
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:05,099
The whole school knows about it.

315
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,476
I mean, it's kinda hard to miss.

316
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:09,604
Well, did you know that
I'm the one who froze it?

317
00:12:09,604 --> 00:12:10,688
Huh?

318
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:12,857
If you ride the wall
with your Air Trecks,

319
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:15,526
could you make it to
the top of the clock?

320
00:12:15,526 --> 00:12:16,861
What, are you kiddin' me?

321
00:12:16,861 --> 00:12:17,862
Piece of cake.

322
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:20,365
Once we're up there,
then what do we do?

323
00:12:20,365 --> 00:12:23,243
I want you to fix the clock
so time can move again.

324
00:12:23,243 --> 00:12:25,036
Huh, but why do you need us?

325
00:12:25,036 --> 00:12:26,371
Can't you do it yourself?

326
00:12:26,371 --> 00:12:29,374
Wait, so you mean it's not
just there for decoration?

327
00:12:29,374 --> 00:12:30,625
It really is broken?

328
00:12:30,625 --> 00:12:31,876
That's what I was wondering.

329
00:12:31,876 --> 00:12:33,169
If it was broken,
it seems like

330
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:34,754
they would've fixed
it by now, right?

331
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:36,881
You see that little
door way up there?

332
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:38,716
That's the only
way to get inside.

333
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:39,801
That's dumb.

334
00:12:39,801 --> 00:12:41,844
The AV room is right
next to the clock.

335
00:12:41,844 --> 00:12:44,222
You should be able to get
in there, shouldn't you?

336
00:12:44,222 --> 00:12:45,390
That's right,

337
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:47,308
but you can't reach
the controls from there.

338
00:12:47,308 --> 00:12:49,769
The two rooms are separated
by a really thick wall.

339
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:51,187
What the hell, that sucks.

340
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,189
Were the architects
drunk or something?

341
00:12:53,189 --> 00:12:55,316
Yeah, stupid drunk architects.

342
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,402
It's supposedly
maintenance‐free.

343
00:12:57,402 --> 00:12:59,779
It sets itself by some
kind of time signal,

344
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:02,198
so there shouldn't ever
be a need to go up there.

345
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,200
Oh, like the clock
on a computer, huh?

346
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:06,703
I think to adjust it,
they use like radio waves.

347
00:13:06,703 --> 00:13:09,080
Guys, it doesn't
really matter, does it?

348
00:13:09,080 --> 00:13:11,958
You know, I was once
a student at this school.

349
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:14,294
I was really
scatterbrained and clumsy.

350
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:16,379
I had problems
just like you guys.

351
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:19,757
I did bad in class, I was
late for school every day,

352
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,760
and Mr. Orihara was
always chewing me out.

353
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,762
He still chews you out.

354
00:13:24,762 --> 00:13:26,431
Mari, why?

355
00:13:26,431 --> 00:13:29,225
Why do you insist on
making my job so hard?

356
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:32,270
He was my homeroom teacher
back when I was in your grade.

357
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:35,189
It was his first year,
so he was a little high strung.

358
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,399
He looks the same to me.

359
00:13:36,399 --> 00:13:38,151
No, look, he's
missing his stubble.

360
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:39,485
I can see his uvula.

361
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:42,655
Why can't you take this
seriously and get here on time?

362
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:45,616
That's mean, I'm always serious!

363
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:46,826
You were a hottie.

364
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:48,453
‐Yeah.
‐She looks the same.

365
00:13:48,453 --> 00:13:51,122
Do you think we can get her
to take her clothes off?

366
00:13:51,122 --> 00:13:52,665
Hey, this isn't a porno.

367
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:54,500
Oh, so you're
really serious, huh?

368
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,335
In that case, if you're
late again tomorrow,

369
00:13:56,335 --> 00:13:57,962
then you're gonna be held back!

370
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:59,922
No!

371
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:03,217
I had to get to school
by 8:30 the next morning,

372
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:04,677
no excuses.

373
00:14:04,677 --> 00:14:07,055
But, you know how that goes.

374
00:14:07,055 --> 00:14:12,602
♪

375
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:14,729
They were all
pretty stupid reasons.

376
00:14:14,729 --> 00:14:16,230
Yeah, but it's funny to watch.

377
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:18,149
And I didn't do it
on purpose either.

378
00:14:18,149 --> 00:14:20,651
‐That's kinda depressing.
‐I can't be late...

379
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:22,945
And no matter
how hard I tried...

380
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:24,906
I can't be late,
I can't be late!

381
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,076
I can't be late,
I can't be late,

382
00:14:28,076 --> 00:14:31,162
I can't be late, I can't be
late, I can't be late, I‐‐

383
00:14:31,162 --> 00:14:32,580
‐(meow)
‐Huh?

384
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,504
Uh, kitty cat?

385
00:14:39,504 --> 00:14:43,883
(meowing)

386
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:44,759
(giggling)

387
00:14:44,759 --> 00:14:47,303
Where are you going,
little kitty?

388
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,722
You're so cute!

389
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:52,100
(squawking)

390
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:56,604
♪

391
00:14:56,604 --> 00:15:00,024
Oh, no, what should I
do, what should I do?

392
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:02,568
There's no point in
going to school now, right?

393
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:06,197
I got distracted by that
kitty and lost track of time.

394
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:07,990
I should just go home.

395
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:09,992
So why am I still running?

396
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:11,994
Why am I still going to school?

397
00:15:11,994 --> 00:15:14,872
I'm sure Mr. Orihara's
left already.

398
00:15:14,872 --> 00:15:16,666
I should just turn around.

399
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:18,543
I should just give up.

400
00:15:18,543 --> 00:15:20,962
But I... I...

401
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:26,592
(slow footsteps)

402
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:33,224
(soft whimpering)

403
00:15:33,224 --> 00:15:35,143
Well, well, well!

404
00:15:35,143 --> 00:15:37,228
You made it on time for once.

405
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,312
What?

406
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:46,612
♪

407
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,114
Class is about to start.

408
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:50,408
Hurry up and get
to your classroom.

409
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:52,451
(whimpering)

410
00:15:52,451 --> 00:15:57,957
♪

411
00:15:57,957 --> 00:16:00,835
(wailing)

412
00:16:00,835 --> 00:16:04,255
♪

413
00:16:04,255 --> 00:16:07,091
Hurry along or I'll make
