414
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:09,594
No, don't, I'm coming!

415
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:12,847
(crying)

416
00:16:12,847 --> 00:16:14,974
Time was put on hold,

417
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:18,060
but my life was moving forward.

418
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:20,479
It's strange,
but since that day,

419
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:23,399
it's like my
feelings have stopped.

420
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:26,277
When I was sitting
there in the classroom,

421
00:16:26,277 --> 00:16:28,279
I decided that when I grow up,

422
00:16:28,279 --> 00:16:30,364
I wanted to be a teacher.

423
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:33,201
(ATs whirring)

424
00:16:33,201 --> 00:16:36,871
So all I gotta do is
make the clock move, right?

425
00:16:36,871 --> 00:16:39,790
♪

426
00:16:41,042 --> 00:16:42,877
(scraping)

427
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,383
That's high.

428
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:53,596
It's just a straight ride up
with nothing to grind on.

429
00:16:53,596 --> 00:16:55,473
I gotta come up with something.

430
00:16:55,473 --> 00:16:57,350
This is different from before.

431
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:59,227
He doesn't have
much to work with,

432
00:16:59,227 --> 00:17:00,228
and the thing is,

433
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:01,687
if he doesn't grab
onto the clock,

434
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:03,439
then the fall could kill him.

435
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,440
Oh, man.

436
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,526
You really think he can do it?

437
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:11,155
There's no easy trick
to make this work.

438
00:17:11,155 --> 00:17:14,742
Speed, angle,
it's a one‐shot deal.

439
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:17,536
(whirring)

440
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:27,713
♪

441
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:28,756
(grunting)

442
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:34,387
♪

443
00:17:34,387 --> 00:17:35,930
‐Ah!
‐Oh, shit!

444
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:37,640
‐Ah!
‐Ikki!

445
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:48,526
♪

446
00:17:48,526 --> 00:17:51,028
I know you don't
think much of me,

447
00:17:51,028 --> 00:17:54,073
and I know I make
a lot of stupid mistakes,

448
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:57,118
as a teacher and as a person,

449
00:17:57,118 --> 00:18:00,496
and I also know I still
have a long way to go...

450
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:04,041
♪

451
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,835
...but know this:

452
00:18:05,835 --> 00:18:08,546
Every day, I'm gonna do my best,

453
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:10,214
and every day,

454
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:13,342
I'm gonna move forward.

455
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:15,678
(tank rumbling)

456
00:18:15,678 --> 00:18:17,555
♪

457
00:18:17,555 --> 00:18:19,682
Spinning Wall Ride!

458
00:18:19,682 --> 00:18:20,975
(gasping)

459
00:18:20,975 --> 00:18:24,520
‐Overbank 1800!
‐Overbank 1800!

460
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:27,815
♪

461
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:29,859
(chuckling)

462
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:33,779
♪

463
00:18:33,779 --> 00:18:35,406
Oh, yeah.

464
00:18:35,406 --> 00:18:40,202
♪

465
00:18:40,202 --> 00:18:41,912
Way to go, Buccha!

466
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:44,624
You saved his life.

467
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,584
I didn't do anything, really.

468
00:18:46,584 --> 00:18:49,003
It takes something special
to pull off a wall spin

469
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:50,671
from that position.

470
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,882
I doubt I could've
done it myself.

471
00:18:52,882 --> 00:18:53,883
(smack, groan)

472
00:18:53,883 --> 00:18:57,386
This isn't the same Ikki
that battled with me.

473
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:59,972
This is a man with real wings.

474
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:03,601
♪

475
00:19:03,601 --> 00:19:06,437
Thank you.

476
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,105
Thank you so much.

477
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:17,448
♪

478
00:19:17,448 --> 00:19:18,658
(powering down)

479
00:19:18,658 --> 00:19:19,617
(chuckling)

480
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:20,868
All right, game's over,

481
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:22,286
you stinkin' brats!

482
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,996
(laughing)

483
00:19:23,996 --> 00:19:25,831
I knew you'd come!

484
00:19:25,831 --> 00:19:28,668
Come on, you punks really
think you can outsmart me?

485
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:30,961
Here to steal the test, are ya?

486
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:33,798
(echoed rolling)

487
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:35,675
Huh?

488
00:19:35,675 --> 00:19:38,010
(clattering)

489
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:40,096
I found this up on the clock.

490
00:19:40,096 --> 00:19:41,931
That little wheel's
been stopping time

491
00:19:41,931 --> 00:19:43,391
for all these years.

492
00:19:43,391 --> 00:19:45,434
Tom‐Tom said she was
the one who did it,

493
00:19:45,434 --> 00:19:48,020
but I don't think that's true.

494
00:19:48,020 --> 00:19:50,481
Looks like it's
working fine now.

495
00:19:50,481 --> 00:19:51,857
That's weird.

496
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:54,568
♪

497
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:57,446
It was too small to
see it from the ground,

498
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,990
but the problem was
on the clock face,

499
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:02,451
not the inside.

500
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:05,162
It's a funny thing to
find stuck up there,

501
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:06,372
don't you think?

502
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:07,832
So what?

503
00:20:07,832 --> 00:20:10,543
Eight years ago, some dude
flew all the way up there

504
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:13,295
to stop time for a girl.

505
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:16,549
Thought that was
kinda cool, that's all.

506
00:20:16,549 --> 00:20:19,593
Pretty crazy, huh?

507
00:20:19,593 --> 00:20:22,805
I was hoping you wouldn't
find out about that.

508
00:20:22,805 --> 00:20:25,182
You still have to take
the exams, you know!

509
00:20:25,182 --> 00:20:27,893
I won't let you off,
even if you beg for mercy!

510
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:31,689
You're gonna cry when
you see the questions!

511
00:20:31,689 --> 00:20:34,358
We'll see about that, won't we?

512
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:35,943
Thank you so much.

513
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:37,361
Here you are.

514
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:39,363
This is the reward
I promised you.

515
00:20:39,363 --> 00:20:40,364
It's the copy

516
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:42,533
of the supplementary
test and answer key.

517
00:20:42,533 --> 00:20:46,495
Yes, yes, I would say it was
a sweet deal for both of us.

518
00:20:46,495 --> 00:20:48,748
You're such an evil little boy.

519
00:20:48,748 --> 00:20:51,375
You flatter me, but I
still have a lot to learn.

520
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:54,295
After all, I'm not
nearly as evil as you.

521
00:20:54,295 --> 00:20:56,756
(chanting laughter)

522
00:20:56,756 --> 00:21:00,634
♪

523
00:21:00,634 --> 00:21:02,720
Okay, brats, let's get started.

